The President released a statement praising the National Broadband Plan, stating that it will bring about an era of innovation, job creation, and improved access to information. He emphasized the importance of expanding broadband across the country to promote economic growth and shared prosperity. The President also commended the efforts of the Chairman, Commissioners, and staff of the FCC in developing the plan. He mentioned that his administration will continue to work towards making America's broadband infrastructure the world's most powerful platform for economic growth, including improving access to mobile broadband and supporting a nationwide public safety wireless broadband network.